      "role": "user",
      "content": "I'll look into winsorization. My main worry is that if I just delete them, I might be throwing away the most interesting parts of the dataset. If I can't figure out if they're errors or just extreme legitimate cases, is there a specific type of model that's better at handling that kind of \"unpredictable\" noise without just crashing or getting heavily biased by the outliers?",
