      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If you suspect the anomalies represent real but highly variable underlying phenomena, moving away from standard linear regression is advisable. Consider using tree-based models like Random Forests or Gradient Boosting Machines, as these models are inherently non-parametric and are much more robust to outliers than OLS. These ensemble methods model the relationship through decision boundaries rather than strictly relying on the mean and variance of the residuals, thus mitigating the outlier's disproportionate influence.",
